description: "Use when updating the local repo before template merges or other sync tasks: switch to main, pull latest, and fetch all remotes. Often used as the first step before template-merging (e.g. 'update from template')."
alwaysApply: false
---

Execute the following steps.

1. **Update your local main branch**
   Switch to the main branch and pull the latest changes.

2. **Fetch all remotes**
   Fetch all remotes to get the latest changes from the remote repositories.
